  "jei.central_heater.burnt_woods.description": "Wood that has been charred by intense heat. You can discover a lot of them after a intense forest fire, possible to artificially create them by stoves. You can strip it with an Axe to chip away the charred layer and produce Charcoal.",
  "jei.central_heater.blazing_furnace.description": "A mystical furnace that burns Soul Sand or Soul Soil instead of standard fuel. It performs 'Haunting', transforming items into their magical or Nether counterparts (e.g., Sweet Berries to Glow Berries).",
  "jei.central_heater.blazing_furnace_minecart.description": "A variant of the Furnace Minecart that runs exclusively on Soul Fuels. It burns hotter and provides stronger thrust than its standard coal-burning counterpart.",
  "jei.central_heater.sturdy_brick.description": "A dense, heat-resistant composite. While difficult to enchant, tools and armor made from Sturdy Brick rival the durability of Diamond, making them excellent for early-to-mid game survival.",
  "jei.central_heater.sturdy_tank.description": "A reinforced container capable of withstanding extreme temperatures. Unlike standard Glass Bottles, the Sturdy Tank can safely store and transport Lava.",
  "jei.central_heater.fire_ash.description": "The powdery residue left behind after solid fuel has been completely consumed. It can be used as a binding agent or crafting ingredient.",
  "jei.central_heater.scorched_dust.description": "The Nether counterpart to Fire Ash. This gritty dust remains when Nether-based items are incinerated in Soul Fire.",

